[SN]TITLE[SN]
Motorcyclist killed in Newport accident named

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorcyclist who died following an accident on Newport's Eastern Distributor Road has been named as 35-year-old Robert William Freeman from Bristol.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The A4810 between the Tesco Distribution Centre and Gwent Europark near Magor was closed after the incident at 01:45 GMT on Tuesday.
No other vehicle was involved, and an appeal has been made for witnesses.
Police said Mr Freeman's family is being supported by specialist officers.
